On Friday, November 05, 2004, at 04:57PM, Casting Fool <jester(-at-)cfnson.com> wrote:

>I was wondering what purpose the two holes with welded nuts are for.  I
>figure that the cutout goes towards the bottom when the bracket's mounted,
>putting the holes at the bottom of the bracket, but could not for the life
>of me figure out what the two holes/nuts were for.  Does anyone know?

If they are at the bottom it's for securing a wide 5 tire (5x205) with two lug bolts. It's a universal tire mount: the three studs are for 5x112 (71-79) wheels.

